briefdescription.para: Constructs a ReadContextBuilder with required parameters.

parameterdescription.para: The root path of the table.

briefdescription.para: Set the schema fields to read from the table.

detaileddescription.para: If not set, all fields from the table schema will be read. This is useful for projection pushdown to reduce I/O and improve performance by reading only the required columns.

parameterdescription.para: Vector of field names to read from the table.

simplesect.para: Reference to this builder for method chaining.
Currently supports top-level field selection. Future versions may support nested field selection using ArrowSchema for more granular projection

briefdescription.para: Set the schema fields to read from the table.

detaileddescription.para: If not set, all fields from the table schema will be read. This is useful for projection pushdown to reduce I/O and improve performance by reading only the required columns.

parameterdescription.para: Vector of field ids to read from the table.

simplesect.para: Reference to this builder for method chaining.
Currently supports top-level field selection. Future versions may support nested field selection using ArrowSchema for more granular projection.
SetReadFieldIds() and SetReadSchema() are mutually exclusive. Calling both will ignore the read schema set by SetReadSchema().

briefdescription.para: Set a configuration options map to set some option entries which are not defined in the table schema or whose values you want to overwrite.

simplesect.para: The options map will clear the options added by AddOption() before.
Reference to this builder for method chaining.

briefdescription.para: Add a single configuration option which is not defined in the table schema or whose value you want to overwrite.

detaileddescription.para:
If you want to add multiple options, call AddOption() multiple times or use SetOptions() instead.
key
The option key.
value
The option value.
Reference to this builder for method chaining.

briefdescription.para: Set a predicate for filtering data during reading.

detaileddescription.para: The predicate is used for both partition pruning and data filtering. It can significantly improve performance by reducing the amount of data that needs to be read and processed.

parameterdescription.para: Shared pointer to the predicate for data filtering.

simplesect.para: Reference to this builder for method chaining.

briefdescription.para: Whether to perform precise filtering according to predicates for data read from format reader.

parameterdescription.para: Whether to enable precise filtering (default: false)

simplesect.para: Reference to this builder for method chaining.

briefdescription.para: Enable or disable prefetching of data batches from individual files.

detaileddescription.para: When enabled, the reader will prefetch multiple batches in parallel to improve throughput by overlapping I/O with computation. This is particularly beneficial for high-latency storage systems.

simplesect.para: Reference to this builder for method chaining.

briefdescription.para: Set prefetch cache mode for read operations.

detaileddescription.para:
A prefetch cache is used to prebuffer data ranges before they are needed, which can improve read performance by reducing redundant I/O operations.
mode
(default: PrefetchCacheMode::ALWAYS)
Reference to this builder for method chaining.

briefdescription.para: Set the cache configuration for prefetch read operations.

simplesect.para: Reference to this builder for method chaining.

briefdescription.para: Set the total number of batches to prefetch across all files.

detaileddescription.para: This controls the memory usage and parallelism of the prefetching mechanism. Higher values can improve throughput but consume more memory.

parameterdescription.para: Total number of batches to prefetch (default: 600)

simplesect.para: Reference to this builder for method chaining.

briefdescription.para: Set the maximum number of parallel prefetch operations.

detaileddescription.para: This limits the number of concurrent I/O operations to prevent overwhelming the storage system or consuming excessive system resources.

simplesect.para: Reference to this builder for method chaining.

briefdescription.para: Enable or disable multi-threaded row-to-batch conversion in merge-on-read scenarios.

detaileddescription.para: When enabled, multiple threads are used to convert row data to batch format during merge operations, which can improve performance for CPU-intensive merge operations.

parameterdescription.para: Whether to enable multi-threaded conversion (default: false)

simplesect.para: Reference to this builder for method chaining.

briefdescription.para: Set the number of threads for row-to-batch conversion in merge-on-read scenarios.

detaileddescription.para: This controls the parallelism of row-to-batch conversion during merge operations. Higher values can improve performance but may affect result ordering.

simplesect.para: Reference to this builder for method chaining.
If thread_number > 1, Arrow batches from the reader may not be in primary key order.

briefdescription.para: Set custom memory pool for memory management.

simplesect.para: Reference to this builder for method chaining.
If not set, the default system memory pool will be used.

briefdescription.para: Set custom executor for task execution.

simplesect.para: Reference to this builder for method chaining.
If not set, the default system executor will be used.

briefdescription.para: Set the table schema as a string to avoid schema loading I/O operations.

detaileddescription.para: This optimization allows the reader to use a pre-loaded schema instead of reading it from the table metadata, which can improve performance especially in scenarios with many small read operations.

parameterdescription.para: String representation of the table schema.

simplesect.para: Reference to this builder for method chaining.
The user must ensure that the schema string is valid and matches the table.
If not set, the schema will be loaded from the table path.

briefdescription.para: Set the specific branch to read from in a versioned table.

detaileddescription.para: Paimon supports branching for data versioning and time travel queries. This method allows reading from a specific branch instead of the main branch.

parameterdescription.para: Name of the branch to read from.

simplesect.para: Reference to this builder for method chaining.
Default branch is "main" if not specified.

briefdescription.para: Sets a mapping from URI schemes (e.g., "file", "oss") to registered file system identifiers.

detaileddescription.para: This allows selecting different pre-registered file system implementations based on the URI scheme at runtime.

parameterdescription.para: Map from URI scheme (like "oss") to the corresponding file system identifier.

simplesect.para: Reference to this builder for method chaining.

listitem.para: This method is intended for environments where multiple file systems are pre-registered.
The specified identifiers must correspond to file systems that have been registered at compile time or initialization.
Cannot be used together with WithFileSystem().
If not set, use default file system (configured in Options::FILE_SYSTEM). Example: builder.WithFileSystemSchemeToIdentifierMap({{"oss", "jindo"}, {"file", "local"}});

briefdescription.para: Sets a custom file system instance to be used for all file operations in this read context.

detaileddescription.para: This bypasses the global file system registry and uses the provided implementation directly.

simplesect.para: Reference to this builder for method chaining.
If not set, use default file system (configured in Options::FILE_SYSTEM)

briefdescription.para: Build and return a ReadContext instance with input validation.

simplesect.para: Result containing the constructed ReadContext or an error status.

briefdescription.para: ReadContextBuilder used to build a ReadContext, has input validation.
